radiographic_examinations.findings: Closure of the neovascular membrane, no evident subretinal fluid.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Visual acuity improved from 20/60 to 20/40 after 3 weeks, but decreased to 20/50 after 9 weeks with a small area of shallow subretinal fluid observed.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Microscopic hyperfluorescent spot at the site of previously active CNV and a small area of shallow subretinal fluid.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Visual acuity remained stable at 20/60 with no significant changes in clinical manifestation or fluorescein angiogram study after 34 weeks.
